ROC curves for NeuroMab data

Jesse Leigh Patsolic

files <- grep("*csv", dir("../", full.names = TRUE), value=TRUE)
names <- file_path_sans_ext(grep("*csv", dir("../"), value=TRUE))

dat <- lapply(files, read.csv, header=TRUE)

d0 <- lapply(dat, 
    function(x){
        d0 <- x[, -1]
        Xs <- d0[,c(1:2)]
        Ys <- d0[,-c(1:2)]
        dd <- data.frame(Xs, melt(Ys, measure.vars= names(Ys)))
        dout <- dd[complete.cases(dd),]
        return(dout)
    })

names(d0) <- names
DenPro <- lapply(d0, 
      function(d){
          ggplot(d, aes(x = Protein.ELISA, group = as.factor(value), col =as.factor(value))) + 
          #geom_histogram(position = 'identity', binwidth = 0.01, alpha = 0.2) + 
          geom_density() + 
          theme(legend.position = "none") +
          facet_grid(variable ~ .)
      })

DenCell <- lapply(d0, 
      function(d){
          ggplot(d, aes(x = Cell.ELISA, group = as.factor(value), col =as.factor(value))) + 
          #geom_histogram(position = 'identity',bins = 50, alpha = 0.2) +
          theme(legend.position = "none") +
          geom_density() + 
          facet_grid(variable ~ .)
      })
d1 <- lapply(d0, function(v){
               v[v$variable == "IHC",]
      })

d2 <- lapply(d0, function(v){
               v[v$variable == "IB",]
      })
rets <- c("threshold", "specificity", "sensitivity", "accuracy", "tn",
          "tp", "fn", "fp", "npv", "ppv", "1-specificity", "1-sensitivity",
          "1-accuracy", "1-npv", "1-ppv")
rrP <- list()
for(i in 1:length(d1)){
rrP[[i]] <- roc(d1[[i]]$value ~ d1[[i]]$Protein.ELISA, ret = rets)
}


rrC <- list()
for(i in 1:length(d1)){
rrC[[i]] <- roc(d1[[i]]$value ~ d1[[i]]$Cell.ELISA)
}

theta <- -pi/4
rotM <- matrix(c(cos(theta), sin(theta), -sin(theta), cos(theta)), 2,2)

rrAP <- lapply(rrP, function(r){ 
               wm <- which.max((as.matrix(cbind(r$spec, r$sens)) %*% rotM)[,2])
               as.matrix(cbind(r$spec, r$sens))[wm,]
          })

rrAC <- lapply(rrC, function(r){ 
               wm <- which.max((as.matrix(cbind(r$spec, r$sens)) %*% rotM)[,2])
               as.matrix(cbind(r$spec, r$sens))[wm,]
          })

Explaination of ROC images

For each experiment we have an empirical joint distribution for Protein.ELISA and Cell.ELISA. We divide each ragne into approximatly 15 bins and use those bins to threashold our classifier. For each pair of thresholds we compute the Sensitivity, Specificity, and Accuracy, i.e. for each poitn \(X\) we use the clasifier
\(g_n(X) = 1\ if\ Protein.ELISA > a\ AND\ Cell.ELISA > b\)
\(g_n(X) = 0\ otherwise\)

An example usign \(a = 0.85\) and \(b = 6.0e7\) is plotted below.

ROC curves

Protein for IHC

par(mfrow = c(2,3))
for(p in 1:length(rrP)){
  plot(rrP[[p]], main = paste(names(d1)[p],"\n", "AUC=",round(rrP[[p]]$auc,3)))
  abline(v = rrAP[[p]][1], h = rrAP[[p]][2], col = 'red')
}
